Flagging something that needs your attention before tonight's event.

I completed my review of the latest Contoso partnership NDA draft (v4, received Thursday). Section 7.3 contains a non-compete clause that is significantly broader than what we negotiated. As drafted, it would restrict Microsoft's AI partnership activities across ALL verticals — including healthcare and financial services — for 24 months post-termination. That's not what we agreed to. The original scope was limited to Contoso's specific market segments.

My recommendation: Do NOT sign this version. I've sent markup back to Contoso's counsel requesting the clause be narrowed to match the negotiated terms. Expecting their response Monday or Tuesday.

More importantly: I understand David Park is attending your event tonight. Please do not discuss specific partnership terms, exclusivity arrangements, or anything that could be construed as M&A negotiation until this clause is resolved. General relationship-building is fine — just stay away from the commercial specifics.

I'm available by phone today if you want a 5-minute briefing before the event. Otherwise, just read this email and you're covered.

